Claims 1 A video decoding device, comprising: a processor configured to: identify a reference block of a video block; derive a spatial convolutional filter associated with the reference block based on a reference block template and a template of the video block; derive a prediction sample of the video block by applying the spatial convolutional filter to the reference block; and decode the video block based on the prediction sample of the video block. 2. The device of claim 1 , wherein the processor is further configured to: identify a second reference block of the video block; derive a second spatial convolutional filter associated with the second reference block based on a second reference block template and a second template of the video block; and derive a second prediction sample of the video block by applying the second spatial convolutional filter to the second reference block, wherein the video block is decoded based on the first prediction sample and the second prediction sample of the video block. 3. The device of any of claims 1 or 2, wherein the processor is further configured to: modify the spatial convolutional filter by adding one or more of a quadratic term, a cross-prediction term, or a gradient term to the spatial convolutional filter, wherein the prediction sample of the video block is derived by applying the modified spatial convolutional filter to the reference block. 4. The device of any of claims 1 through 3, wherein the processor is further configured to: identify a second reference block of the video block; derive a second spatial convolutional filter associated with a second reference block; modify the second spatial convolutional filter by adding one or more of a quadratic term, a crossprediction term, or a gradient term to the second spatial convolutional filter; and derive a second prediction sample of the video block by applying the modified second spatial convolutional filter to the second reference block, wherein the video block is decoded based on the first prediction sample and the second prediction sample of the video block. 5. The device of any of claims 1 through 4, wherein the processor being configured to derive the prediction sample of the video block by applying the spatial convolutional filter to the reference block comprises the processor being configured to: receive a filter set index configured to indicate a selected filter set among a plurality of filter sets, wherein the spatial convolutional filter to apply to the reference block is derived based on the filter set index. 6. The device of claim 5, wherein the plurality of filter sets comprises one or more of a first filter learned from a left template, a second filter learned from a top template, or a third filter learned from a combined left top template of the coding block. 7. A video encoding device, comprising: a processor configured to: identify a reference block of a video block; derive a spatial convolutional filter associated with the reference block based on a reference block template and a template of the video block; derive a prediction sample of the video block by applying the spatial convolutional filter to the reference block; and encode the video block based on the prediction sample of the video block. 8. The device of claim 7, wherein the processor is further configured to: identify a second reference block of the video block; derive a second spatial convolutional filter associated with the second reference block based on a second reference block template and a second template of the video block; and derive a second prediction sample of the video block by applying the second spatial convolutional filter to the second reference block, wherein the video block is encoded based on the first prediction sample and the second prediction sample of the video block. 9. The device of any of claims 7 or 8, wherein the processor is further configured to: modify the spatial convolutional filter by adding one or more of a quadrat